<task id="task-43" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Create a new test case in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/></title><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context class="- topic/section task/context ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">To create a new test case in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/>, first, open your desired Katalon project. You can learn more about how to open projects at: <xref href="../../Manage_Projects/Manage_Test_Project/Manage_Test_Project_Overview/Manage_test_project.dita" class="- topic/xref ">Manage test project in Katalon Studio overview</xref></p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">On the right side of <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/>, you can see the <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-tests-explorer" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/> section containing access to all folders of your projects. There are three ways to create a new test case in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/>:</p>
        </context><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">From the main toolbar, click on <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Create new Test Case</uicontrol>.</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><image width="700" href="image/ks-841-hero.png" class="- topic/image "/></info><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">Or, in the <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-tests-explorer" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/> panel, right-click on the <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-test-case" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/> folder and select <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-new" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/> &gt; <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-test-case" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/>.</info><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><image width="500" href="image/ks-841-new-test-case.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">new test case in test explorer</alt></image></info><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">Alternatively, you can also go to <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-file" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/> &gt; <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-new" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/> &gt; <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-test-case" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/> from the main menu.</info><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                    <note type="tip" class="- topic/note ">
                        <ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li ">
                                <p class="- topic/p ">For better management, you can also create a new folder by selecting <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "><uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-test-cases" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/></b> &gt; <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-new" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/> &gt; <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text-2/ks-folder" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/>, then create new test cases inside that folder.</p>
                            </li></ul>
                    </note>
                </info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">The <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-new-test-case" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/> dialog appears. Enter your test case name, description, and tag. You can organize your project more efficiently by creating relevant test case names, tags, and providing detailed descriptions.</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><image width="500" href="../Images/tc-new-test-case.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Create new test case dialog</alt></image></info><stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
                    <p class="- topic/p ">After you are done, click&#160;<uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-ok" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/>. <note class="- topic/note ">
                            <ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li ">
                                    <p class="- topic/p ">Tags can be useful for large project management. You can learn how to manipulate tag properties at <xref href="../../../Organize/Manage_Tests/Dynamic_Test_Suite/Test_Case_Management_With_Tags/intro-test-case-management-with-tags.dita" class="- topic/xref ">Test Case Management With Tags</xref>.</p>
                                </li></ul>
                        </note></p>
                </stepresult></step></steps><result class="- topic/section task/result ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">A new test case is created inside the <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-test-case" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/> folder.</p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">Once a new test case is created, it is opened in <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-manual" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/> view. This view allows you to create automated tests with little programming skills required. You can switch to the <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-script" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/> tab to edit in Script view.</p>
                <image href="../../../../Global_reuse/Images_warehouse/Katalon_Studio/Toolbars_and_views/Editor_view/ks-manual.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">The manual view</alt></image>
        </result></taskbody></task>